line_1: Now swallows build, and lonely ravens croak.
line_2: And where of old rose high the social smoke,
That raven on yon left-hand oak

line_1: Near her stick-built nest doth croak,
Full on the left, with hideous croak,
line_2: Stood flutt'ring on a blasted oak.

line_1: Whence Owls their Dirges sing, and Ravens croak:
line_2: Untun'd, shall hang upon this blasted Oak,

line_1: Something was meant by that ill boading Croak
line_2: Of the prophetick Raven from the Oak,

line_1: Something was meant by that ill boading Croak
line_2: Which strait by Light'ning was in Shivers broke.
